        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener><dateline><date when="1914-10-25">Oct. 25, 1914</date></dateline><salute>My dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet <add place="above" type="insertion" rend="pencil">Monroe</add><!--The addition was not in the original transcription - blw--></persName>:</salute></opener>
                <p>I have never written you but I have sent you a telegram thanking you for your courtesy in substituting <title key="bombardment" level="a">&quot;The Bombardment&quot;</title> for <title key="allies" level="a">&quot;The Allies.&quot;</title> I am sorry for the poor, crowded-out one, but I have no doubt that you will give me every chance in <title key="poetry" level="j">another number</title>. I got <title key="balladOfFootment" level="a">&quot;The Ballad of Footmen&quot;</title> safely back. Of course you do not want any more war poems now.</p>
                <p>I notice what you say about having <persName>Mr. Schwill</persName> <!-- Not in personography, listed as not being a priority in the letter metadata, tagged but didn't include a key -blw --> review <title key="youAndI" level="m">your book</title>, I have no doubt he would do it extremely well. Should he decline, however, and you want my services, just say so.</p>
                <p>I am just off for <placeName key="nyc">New York</placeName> to see <orgName key="macmillan">Macmillan</orgName> about <title key="some_imagist_poets" level="m">our anthology</title>. I shall hope to get hold of <persName key="vachel_lindsay">Mr. Lindsay</persName> there because I should like to meet him.</persName>
                <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
